DTSTART:20260305T220000Z
DTEND:20260305T233000Z
LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
SUMMARY:ACC's Over A Cup of Tea with Hoosier Asian American Power Panel: 
 Civic Engagement in Action
DESCRIPTION:Join Hoosier Asian American Power (HAAP) for an engaging comm
 unity conversation on civic engagement and what it means to be Asian Amer
 ican in Indiana right now. This interactive panel invites students to sub
 mit their questions anonymously into a "fishbowl\," and panelists will dr
 aw and respond in real time.  Questions can range from voting and advocac
 y to identity\, belonging\, and how to take meaningful action in this mom
 ent. Whether you're curious\, frustrated\, energized\, or just beginning 
 to explore civic life\, this space is designed for honest dialogue\, shar
 ed learning\, and collective power-building.  Come ready to listen\, ask\
 , and imagine what's possible together.All Indiana University events\, gr
 oups\, activities\, and&#160\;educational\, cultural\, and historical obs
 ervances welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana Univers
 ity community.For more information\, view this event in BeInvolved (https
 ://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12168110).
