BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260306T220000Z
DTEND:20260307T000000Z
LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
SUMMARY:Asian Cultures Around Campus presents a Mini Concert by Shawn Tai
 ryu Head on Shakuhachi
DESCRIPTION:The shakuhachi is a traditional Japanese bamboo flute with a 
 history that spans over 1\,000 years. It is known for its distinctive des
 ign and sound\, and it carries cultural and spiritual significance in Jap
 an. Join us as we learn and appreciate the sound of shakuhachi from the m
 aster himself\, Shawn Tairyu Head. This mini concert is made possible by 
 the Bloomington Symphony Orchestra. A Q and A with Shawn Tairyu Head will
  follow the concert.  Light dinner reception will be served. RSVP by emai
 ling acc@iu.edu (mailto:acc@iu.edu).All Indiana University events\, group
 s\, activities\, and&#160\;educational\, cultural\, and historical observ
 ances welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana University
  community.For more information\, view this event in BeInvolved (https://
 beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11993488).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The shakuhachi is a traditional Japanes
 e bamboo flute with a history that spans over 1\,000 years. It is known f
 or its distinctive design and sound\, and it carries cultural and spiritu
 al significance in Japan. Join us as we learn and appreciate the sound of
  shakuhachi from the master himself\, Shawn Tairyu Head. This mini concer
 t is made possible by the Bloomington Symphony Orchestra. A Q and A with 
 Shawn Tairyu Head will follow the concert.</p><br /><p>  Light dinner rec
 eption will be served. RSVP by emailing <a href="mailto:acc@iu.edu">acc@i
 u.edu</a>.</p><br /><p><span data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">All India
 na University events\, groups\, activities\, and&#160\;educational\, cult
 ural\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and other membe
 rs of the Indiana University community.</span></p><br /><strong>For more 
 information\, <a href="https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11993488">vie
 w this event in BeInvolved</a>.</strong>
